sql:
SELECT models.model_name, experiments.start_time
FROM experiments
INNER JOIN models ON experiments.model_id = models.model_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'minor threshold' refers to a learning rate above 0.01;
- 'intricate visual representations' is defined by the number of data points (signified by commas in the visualization data) being the maximum found in any visualization record;
- 'performance metric' refers to the value derived from the experiment's results;
- 'best performers' means the highest metric values.
